headline: The AI Trade Is Back. This ETF Shows Why.
summary: The AI trade is back, if the GlobalX Artificial Intelligence & Technology exchange-trade fund is any indication.  The ETF has 85 component stocks, ranging from  Tencent Holdings  which comprises 3.9% of the fund, down to  Soundhound  AI, which makes up just 0.2%.

headline: Why Oracle Stock Is Jumping Today
summary: Oracle is teaming up with Texas public safety, providing it with AI-enabled tools.  Stocks across the market saw a boost from Iran's relatively limited response to U.S. strikes.  The jump comes as the S&P 500 and the Nasdaq Composite both had positive days.

headline: C3 AI Appoints Rob Schilling as Executive Vice President and Chief Commercial Officer
summary: REDWOOD CITY, Calif., June 24, 2025--C3 AI (NYSE: AI), the Enterprise AI application software company, today announced the appointment of Rob Schilling as Executive Vice President and Chief Commercial Officer, effective June 16, 2025. With more than two decades of experience driving enterprise software sales, Schilling will now lead C3 AI’s customer-facing operations.

headline: BlackRock launches Texas ETF as state draws investor interest
summary: The Lone Star State's low taxes, business-friendly policies and growing tech and energy sectors have attracted investors and asset managers looking to tap into its long-term growth potential.  BlackRock said iShares Texas Equity ETF will invest in companies headquartered in the state.  The world's largest asset manager said Texas is home to one in ten publicly traded U.S. companies, and that more than 300 firms have relocated their headquarters to the state since 2015.
